---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="Leter abuse reporting policy." />
    <title>Abuse Reporting | leter.net</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="min-h-screen bg-surface">
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-text">‚Üê Back to home</a>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text">Abuse Reporting</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: February 15, 2026</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-muted">
          <p>
            Leter maintains a strict anti-abuse posture. Reports are reviewed to protect users and
            infrastructure integrity.
          </p>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">1. What to report</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Report phishing, spam, malware, impersonation, credential theft, or other harmful
              activity linked to leter.net domains.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">2. What to include</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Include timestamps, sender/recipient details, headers where possible, and a short
              description of the incident.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">3. Contact</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Abuse contact: <span class="text-text">abuse@leter.net</span> (placeholder)
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
